Version: 1.0
Date: [2025-Nov-30]
Author: [Muddasir Khan]

1. Introduction:

1.1) Purpose: 
Provide a platform for customers to order food online from multiple restaurants
restaurant owners to manage menus and orders 
delivery personnel to fulfill deliveries.

1.2) Scope: 
Web & mobile front-ends
backend order/payment services
integration with 3rd-party payment gateways & mapping services.

2. Overall Description:

2.1) User Classes: 
Customers 
Restaurants/Managers 
Delivery Personnel 
Admin.

2.2) Operating Environment: 
Cloud-hosted backend (REST APIs)
mobile apps (iOS/Android) and responsive web.

2.3) Design Constraints: 
PCI-DSS for payments 
data privacy laws (GDPR/PDPA depending on region) 
integrate external maps & payment gateways.


3. Functional Requirements (selected)
•	FR1: User Account Management (register/login)
•	FR2: Browse restaurants and menu items
•	FR3: Add to cart and place order
•	FR4: Payment processing and receipt generation
•	FR5: Order tracking and notifications
•	FR6: Restaurant menu management
•	FR7: Assign and manage deliveries

4. Non-Functional Requirements
•	NFR1: Response Time — 95% of API calls < 2 seconds.
•	NFR2: Availability — 99.9% uptime.
•	NFR3: Security — TLS for all network traffic; tokenization for payment data.
•	NFR4: Scalability — Horizontal scaling for web & API layers.
•	NFR5: Logging & Monitoring — centralized logs and health checks.
